  "What is a probability density function (pdf)?": "什么是概率密度函数 (pdf) ?",
  "A probability density function (pdf) describes the relative likelihood of a continuous random variable taking on given values. The probability of the variable falling in a range [a, b] is the integral of the pdf from a to b. The pdf must be non-negative and integrate to 1 over its entire domain.": "概率密度函数 (pdf) 表示一个连续随机变量使用给定值的相对可能性。 [a, b] 范围内变量的概率是 pdf 从 a 到 b 的有机体。 pdf 必须是非负的, 并在整个域内整合为 1 。",
  "What is a cumulative distribution function (CDF)?": "什么是累积分布函数(CDF)?",
  "The CDF F(x) = P(X <= x) gives the probability that the random variable takes a value less than or equal to x. It is obtained by integrating the pdf from -infinity to x. It is non-decreasing, starting at 0 and approaching 1.": "CDF F(x) = P(X)   x ) 给出随机变量的数值小于或等于 x 的概率。 它通过将pdf从 - 无限到 x 的整合而获得。 它从 0 开始不降为 1 。",
  "What is an 'exponential distribution'?": "什么是“奢侈分配”?",
  "The exponential distribution has pdf f(x) = (1/lambda)*e^(-x/lambda) for x >= 0, where lambda is the mean. It is commonly used to model time between events in a Poisson process, such as waiting times. Its mean and standard deviation are both lambda.": "指数分布为 pdf f(x) = (1/lambda) * e(-x/lambda) = x = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =/ =/ =/ = (x/lambda) = = 0 = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =/ =/ =/ =/ =/ =/ =/ =/ =/ = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =/ =/ = = =/ =/ =/ = = = = = = = = =",
  "What is a 'uniform distribution'?": "什么是“统一分布”?",
  "A uniform distribution on [a, b] assigns equal probability density to all values in the interval: f(x) = 1/(b-a). The mean is (a+b)/2, the midpoint. Examples include randomly choosing a real number between a and b.": "[a, b] 上的统一分布为间隔内的所有值的概率密度相等: f(x) = 1/(b)-a。平均值为 (a+b)/2,中点。示例包括在 a 和 b 之间随机选择一个实际数字。",
  "What is the 'mode' of a continuous probability distribution?": "连续概率分布的“ 模式” 是什么 ?",
  "The mode is the value of x at which the pdf reaches its maximum value. It represents the most likely value (highest probability density). A distribution can have more than one mode (bimodal, multimodal) or no mode.": "模式是 pdf 达到其最大值的 x 值。 它代表最有可能的值( 最高概率密度 ) 。 分布可以有一个以上模式( 双倍模式、 多式联运模式) 或没有模式 。",
  "The lifetime of a lightbulb follows an exponential distribution with a mean of 1000 hours. What is the probability that a randomly selected bulb lasts more than 1500 hours?": "灯泡的寿命沿以 10 小时为平均值的指数分布。随机选择的灯泡的寿命超过 15 小时的概率是多少?",
  "For an exponential distribution with mean lambda = 1000, the pdf is f(x) = (1/1000)*e^(-x/1000). P(X > 1500) = integral from 1500 to infinity of (1/1000)*e^(-x/1000) dx = e^(-1500/1000) = e^(-1.5) = approximately 0.2231.": "对于平均羊羔=1000的指数分布,pdf是 f(x) = 1/1000*(x/1000)。P(X) > 1500) = 1500至无限(1/1000) *(x/1000) dx = e__(-1500/1000) = e(-1500/1000) = (-1.5) = 约0.2231。",
  "A bus arrives at a stop uniformly at random between 8:00 and 8:30 AM. What is the probability that a commuter arriving at 8:10 waits less than 5 minutes?": "八点到八点到八点半之间 公交车平均随机到达一个站点。 8点到十点的通勤者 等待不到5分钟的概率是多少?",
  "Given the commuter arrives at 8:10, the bus must arrive between 8:10 and 8:15 for a wait of less than 5 minutes. But the bus arrives uniformly between 8:00 and 8:30. Given that the bus has not yet arrived by 8:10, we need P(bus arrives in [8:10, 8:15] | bus arrives in [8:10, 8:30]) = 5/20 = 1/4.": "8:10到8:10,8:10到8:15之间必须乘公交车到达,等候时间不到5分钟。但公交车平均在8:00到8:30之间到达。鉴于公交车尚未在8:10到达,我们需要P(公交车抵达时间:[8:10,8:15] +公交车抵达时间:[8:10,8:30] = 5/20 = 1/4)。",
  "The time (in minutes) a customer spends on hold follows an exponential distribution with mean 5 minutes. A customer service manager wants to ensure that 90% of callers wait at most T minutes. What is T?": "客户被搁置的时间(以分钟计)是按指数分布,平均5分钟。 客户服务经理希望确保90%的来电者在最多T分钟时等候。 T是什么?",
  "We need P(X <= T) = 0.9. For exponential with mean 5: P(X <= T) = 1 - e^(-T/5) = 0.9, so e^(-T/5) = 0.1, giving -T/5 = ln(0.1) = -ln(10). Therefore T = 5*ln(10) = approximately 11.51 minutes.": "我们需要P(X) = 0.9。对于5:P(X) = 1 - e(-T/5) = 0.9, 所以e(-T/5) = 0.1, give - T/5 = In(0.1) = -ln(10), 因此T = 5 *ln(10) = 约11.51分钟。",
  "An online store models daily revenue (in thousands of dollars) with pdf f(x) = (3/8)x^2 for 0 <= x <= 2. What is the expected daily revenue?": "网上商店以 pdf f(x) = (3/8x%2) = 0 * x = = 2. 预期的每日收入是多少?",
  "E(X) = integral from 0 to 2 of x * (3/8)x^2 dx = (3/8) * integral from 0 to 2 of x^3 dx = (3/8)[x^4/4] from 0 to 2 = (3/8)(4) = 3/2 = 1.5 (thousands). So the expected daily revenue is $1,500.": "E(X) = 从0到2的有机体",
  "A medical researcher finds that the duration (in days) of a certain illness follows a distribution with pdf f(t) = (1/9)t*e^(-t/3) for t >= 0. What is the expected duration of the illness?": "一位医学研究人员发现,某种疾病的持续时间(天数)是在与pdf f(t) = (1/9)t* e(-t/3)的分布之后,在t  0. 中,该疾病的预期持续时间是多少?",
  "This is a Gamma distribution with shape parameter 2 and rate parameter 1/3. The mean is shape * scale = 2 * 3 = 6 days. Equivalently, E(T) = integral from 0 to infinity of t * (1/9)*t*e^(-t/3) dt = (1/9) * integral of t^2*e^(-t/3) dt = (1/9)*2*(3)^3 = (1/9)*54 = 6.": "这是带有形状参数2和速率参数1/3的伽玛分布。 平均值是形状 * = 2 * 3 = 6 天。 等值, E( T) = 0 到 无限 t * (1/ 9) * (- t) * (- t/3) dt = (1/ 9) * t = 2 * (e) (- t/3) dt = (1/ 9) * = (1/ 9) * * * * * (- t/3) dt = (1/ 9) * (3) 3 = (1/ 9) * 54 = 6 。",
  "A machine component has a failure time modeled by the pdf f(t) = 2e^(-2t) for t >= 0 (time in years). What is the probability the component survives past 1 year?": "机器组件的失败时间由 pdf f( t) = 2e( 2t) 模型为 t  0 ( 年中时间) 。 该组件在过去一年中存活的概率是多少?",
  "P(T > 1) = integral from 1 to infinity of 2e^(-2t) dt = [-e^(-2t)] from 1 to infinity = 0 - (-e^(-2)) = e^(-2) = approximately 0.1353. This exponential distribution has mean 1/2 year, so surviving past 1 year is relatively unlikely.": "P(T > 1) = 从1到无限 2e(-2t) dt = [-e(-2t)] 从1到无限 = 0 - (-e(-2-2) = e(-2) = 约 0. 1353(2001)。这种指数分布平均为 1/2 年,因此过去1 年的存活率相对较小。",
  "A teacher models test scores with the pdf f(x) = (1/50)(x - 50) for 50 <= x <= 60 and f(x) = (1/50)(70 - x) for 60 <= x <= 70. What is the median score?": "以 pdf f(x) = (1/50)(x- 50) = 50  x  60 和 f(x) = (1/50)(70-x) = 60  x  = 70 = 70. 中位数是多少?",
  "This is a triangular distribution symmetric about x = 60. By symmetry, P(X <= 60) = 0.5, so the median is 60. The pdf forms a triangle with peak at x = 60 and base from 50 to 70.": "这是三角分布对称x = 60 对称, P(X) = 60) = 0.5, 所以中位数为 60. pdf 形成三角形, 峰值为 x = 60 , 基数为 50 至 70 。",
  "A weather station records daily rainfall amounts following f(x) = 3(1-x)^2 for 0 <= x <= 1 (in inches). What is the probability of getting more than half an inch of rain?": "气象站记录的每日降雨量为 f(x) = 3(1-x) = 3( 1-x) = 0 = = x = = 1 (英寸) 。 降雨量超过 半 英寸的概率是多少?",
  "P(X > 0.5) = integral from 0.5 to 1 of 3(1-x)^2 dx = 3 * [-(1-x)^3/3] from 0.5 to 1 = [-(1-x)^3] from 0.5 to 1 = (0 - (-1/8)) = 1/8.": "P(X > 0.5) = 0.5至1(3,1-x)2 dx= 3 * [-(1-x)3] 0.5至1= [-(1x)3] = [-(1x)3] = [-(1x)3] = 0.5至1 = (0 - (-1/8) = 1/8) = 1/8。",
  "A pizza delivery company promises delivery within 30 minutes. Delivery times follow a distribution with pdf f(t) = (1/25)(10-t) for 20 <= t <= 30 minutes. What percentage of deliveries arrive late (after 30 minutes)?": "一家比萨饼交货公司承诺在30分钟内交货。交付时间紧随与pdf f(t) = (1/25)(10-t) = (1/25)(10-t) = (1/25)(t) 30分钟的分发之后。 多少比例的交货迟到(30分钟后)?",
  "Since the pdf is zero for t > 30 (the distribution only spans [20, 30]), P(T > 30) = 0. This means 0% of deliveries are late. The distribution is defined to have no probability mass beyond 30 minutes.": "由于 pdf 为零, t > 30 (分布范围仅为 [20, 30] ) , P(T > 30) = 0。 这意味着交付的0 % 迟到。 分配定义为30分钟以上没有概率质量 。"
